WHO   — MIKE TYSON'S PUNCH-OUT!! — the boxing game-world
WHAT  — Mike Tyson's Punch-Out!! — Nintendo's NES classic: the wire-frame Little Mac, Doc Louis in the corner, a gallery of foreign champions across three circuits, the star punch, and a dream fight with Mike Tyson (later Mr. Dream).
WHERE — a 17-year-old, 107-pound underdog from the Bronx who climbs three circuits to a dream fight with Iron Mike  Framework inputs: Punch-Out!!; Little Mac; Doc Louis; Mike Tyson; Mr. Dream; the circuits; the star punch; the tells; the dream fight  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — A boxing game that is really a puzzle: read each champion's tell, dodge / duck / weave, land the counter to earn stars for the uppercut, and survive the giants — to Iron Mike, who can drop you in one punch.
HOW   — Crystallized from Mike Tyson's Punch-Out!! (Nintendo, NES 1987) — the home version of the 1984 arcade Punch-Out!!, with the real heavyweight champ as the final Dream Fight.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The smallest man in the ring reads the biggest, waits for the tell, and answers one punch with the only punch that counts.

